	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="0866"/>
			<p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3054643/budapest.html">Budapest</placeName> reports <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1110" type="subject">War Minister</term> ordered <date when="1942-11-19"
					>November 19th</date> mobilization all able bodied <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864"
					type="subject">Jews</term> born <date from="1909" notAfter="1918">1909-1918</date> for duty <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">work</term> battalions auxiliary <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1086" type="subject">military service</term>. [...]</p>
			<pb n="1" facs="0867"/>
			<p>It is believed likely that many of these <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term>
				will be sent to occupied <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2017370/russian-federation.html">Russian</placeName> territory for
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">manual labor</term> as has been the case with
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews </term>from other Danubian countries. The
				eventual repatriation of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">deported</term> to the East would not appear to be
				envisaged by the present <term ref="#ehri_dr_government_hungarian">Hungarian Government</term> which has recently intensified under
				Nazi inspiration its <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-337" type="subject">anti-Jewish program</term>.</p>
		</body>
